{subhead}Dr. Strange, Web Wanderer{def}{p}
Article by Mark Tierno
{left}
{pp}
Well, if you're seeing this then that means it's not only comming up
on April but you also have the CD edition of AIO.  Not that that
chancges the web sites any, but I thought it worth mentioning.  Usual
ecclectic variety this month, so why don't I just get right into it...
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Evil Overlord Inc.{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.eviloverlord.com/{noitalic}{p}
What if you became the supreme overlord of the world?  What would you
do differnt from previous pretenders to the throne?  Well, herein is a
hillarious list of things all really good overlords shouls do.  Tings
such as "My ventilation ducts will be too small to crawl through" or
"Shooting is not too good for my enemies".  Take a browse, it's funny.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Hats Of Meat{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.hatsofmeat.com/HatsofMeat/{noitalic}{p}
The title says it all.  Yes, pictures of hats made of meat along with
their own version of the history of meat hats.  These people are just
plain crazy.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Atomic Archive{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.atomicarchive.com/index.shtml{noitalic}{p}
The history of th atomic bomb along with the expectd pictures of
things that go boom in a really big way.  Bombs, the history and
development, as well as the science of fission and fusion.
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}The Bobbens Page{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.pboberg.2ya.com{noitalic}{p}
An on-lin version of an also downloadable document listing in
excessive details all the famous and not-so-famous people, companies,
and organizations that have put Amigas to good use.
{pp}
{pp}
{center}{bold}Pick Of The Month{nobold}{left}
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Classic Gaming{nobold}{p}
{italic}http://www.classicgaming.com/{noitalic}{p}
Are you into computer games?  What about some old classics?  Well here
is a site devoted to classic computer gaming.  From the expected Atari
to Apple II, Coleco, Intellivision, Vectrex, arcade games, and a lot
more.  Games and emulators alike, it's all here.
{pp}
For general information there's  articles on the history of computer gaming to repairing your old
NES, Atari 8-bit computers, and the occasional interview.  Visit the
museum of past systems and see how long a history th recent years oif
gaming has developed.  Or see the Game Of The Week for their recent
poick of some past game of merit.  Finally you can see the list of
other hosted sites, conveniently grouped by if they deal in emulators,
gaming utils, information, games, or the worship of particular games
or games series.
{pp}
If you're into classic computer games games, there is no better site
for the subject that I've come across.  So put new life into those old
games and start aiming that browser in this site's direction.
{pp}

